Diagnosis.
Outer orbital angle typically reduced, acuminate (
Figs. 16A
; 
17A, B, E
). Dorsal surface of cheliped merus with depression near anterior margin.

Distribution. Western Atlantic from North Carolina, Bermuda and Gulf of Mexico to southern Brazil (
Coelho et al . 2008
). Depth: shallow subtidal to 90 m ( Powers 1977 ).
